description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kitchen Stores Person&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require a Kitchen Stores Person to work in our main kitchen dealing with the day to day ordering and stock control of the stores.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to assist in the ordering of stock through various company&#39;s and NHS supply chain, receiving of goods, stock control and rotation, recording of deliveries and associated paperwork in accordance to the Food Safety Management System. This position will require close communication with chefs, Team Leaders and the Catering Lead. You will also be required to complete basic cleaning tasks in accordance to Food Safety Management Systems and the maintenance and cleanliness off all storage areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of kitchen work would be advantageous but not essential as full training will be given. Computer skills in word, excel and outlook are a must as well good communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post 1: Monday to Friday 0600-1400&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Andrew Park&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Catering Operational Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;andrewpark@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
